# Hayes Outbreak — GTA-Style Open-World Zombie Survival (Game Concept)

## High Concept
A modern-day, GTA-style open-world zombie survival shooter set in a fictionalized **Hayes, America** inspired by Hays, Kansas, with **Fort Hays State University as the main focal point**. Former FHSU football players and local survivors must navigate a city-wide outbreak where many infected are turned students and townspeople. The world is fully explorable with interiors, roads, campus blocks, and surrounding neighborhoods.

---

## Core Fantasy
- Survive wave pressure while moving freely through a realistic modern city.
- Scavenge weapons, ammo, and gear from walls, lockers, stores, houses, garages, and police/military caches.
- Build your character from basic survivor to elite anti-horde specialist.
- Drive and customize muscle cars (Dodge Charger/Challenger-inspired) and utility vehicles for mobility, rescue, and zombie-clearing.
- Balance risk and reward: zombie packs can overwhelm even armored vehicles and heavily geared players.

---


## GTA-Style Pillars (Zombie Edition)
- **One connected sandbox**: no level-select feel; you can freely roam from campus to downtown to outskirts.
- **Mission + free-roam blend**: story jobs, side activities, random street events, and emergent chaos between missions.
- **Living city simulation**: survivor traffic, faction patrols, looting NPCs, road hazards, and shifting hot zones.
- **Character + vehicle fantasy**: build your survivor and your car identity with visual/performance upgrades.
- **Heat/Threat response loop**: loud actions escalate infected/faction pressure, forcing escapes, stealth, or stand-your-ground fights.

