## Combat, Loot, and Economy

## Weapon Discovery
- Guns spawn on walls, floors, lockers, display racks, and hidden stashes.
- Categories:
  - Sidearms
  - Shotguns
  - SMGs
  - Assault rifles
  - DMR/sniper options
  - Improvised melee (bats, axes, pipe tools)

## Attachments & Gun Upgrades
- Optics, suppressors, compensators, extended mags, laser modules.
- Durability and maintenance for realism.
- Ammo caliber scarcity creates strategic weapon choices.

## Armor & Body Upgrades
- Helmet tiers, chest rigs, trauma plates, tactical clothing.
- Upgrade path examples:
  - Light mobility build
  - Balanced patrol build
  - Heavy breacher build

## Points & Currency Loop
- **Infection Elimination Points (IEP)** for kills, objectives, rescues.
- IEP spent at safehouse terminals, traders, or mobile vendors.
- Additional resources:
  - Scrap (crafting)
  - Fuel (vehicles/generators)
  - Med supplies (healing/boosters)

---

## Vehicle System (Modern Realism)

## Vehicle Types
- **Muscle Cars**: Charger/Challenger-inspired builds for speed and style.
- **SUV/Truck**: Better durability and storage.
- **Utility Vans**: Team support and supply transport.

## Vehicle Customization
- Visual mods: body kits, paint, rims, lighting, decals.
- Performance mods: engine tune, suspension, tires, brakes, transmission.
- Survival mods:
  - Window guards
  - Reinforced bumpers
  - Underbody plating
  - Roof racks for extra storage

## Vehicle Damage & Counterplay
- Zombie impacts damage tires, windshield, radiator, and drivetrain.
- Hitting large hordes can stall/overheat/immobilize vehicle.
- Players must choose when to ram vs. avoid.

